div.div:
URLs look like
Callback-url(send to service, like RuCaptcha/AntiCaptcha):
http://85.255.8.26:8001/<service_name>/<captcha_type>/<queue_name>
New queue-register url:
http://85.255.8.26:8001/register_key
json={
"key": <queue_name>,
"vhost": <vhost_name>
}
<service_name> - "rucaptcha"/"anticaptcha"
<vhost_name> - "rucaptcha_vhost"/"anticaptcha_vhost"
<captcha_type> :
For RuCaptcha - 'fun_captcha', 'image_captcha', 'key_captcha', 'media_captcha', 'recaptcha_captcha','rotate_captcha'
For AntiCaptcha -'image_to_text', 'nocaptcha', 'fun_captcha', 'square_net_text_captcha', 'gee_test_captcha', 'custom_captcha'
<queue_name> - unique name(25 symbols length is a plus). Can use many times.

div.div:
Get answer from RabbitMQ queue
1. Connect to remote queue with <queue_name> param (from `New queue-register url` action)
2. Get from queue last message, check <id>(for RuCaptcha) and <taskId>(for AntiCaptcha), and if all is ok make "Delivery processing acknowledgements from consumer to publisher".
3. Use <code>(for RuCaptcha) and<message>(for AntiCaptcha) from message to solve captcha.

div.h1: Plan for RuCaptcha service and callback
div.p: 1. Register new queue on callback server.
2. Create new captcha-solve task with `pingback` param.
3. You have two variants to get captcha solving data:

3.1 Connect to RabbitMQ queue and wait message. Using this URL to login, and waiting message:
amqp://hardworker_1:password@85.255.8.26:5672/rucaptcha_vhost;
3.2 Send GET requests to our server (and get data from cache);
4. Solve your captcha using <code> from response.

div.h1: Plan for AntiCaptcha service and callback
div.p: 1. Register new queue on callback server.
2. Create new captcha-solve task with `callbackUrl` param.
3. You have two variants to get captcha solving data:

3.1 Connect to RabbitMQ queue and wait message. Using this URL to login, and waiting message:
amqp://hardworker_1:password@85.255.8.26:5672/anticaptcha_vhost;
3.2 Send GET requests to our server (and get data from cache);
4. Solve your captcha using <solution> from response (response similar to the contents of getTaskResult method).
